modules.description: Provides functions to serialize and deserialize OCaml values to and from XML and JSON strings, supporting custom type definitions for RPC communication. Works with OCaml's native types and user-defined variants, records, and sums. Used to encode request parameters and decode responses in distributed systems communicating over text-based protocols.

Generates HTML representations from RPC type definitions, method parameters, and interface structures using specific type handlers. It constructs sidebars, tabs, and structured views for documentation or visualization purposes. Processes boxed type fields, variant tags, and method signatures to produce formatted HTML content.
